            "questionText": "An electromagnet has a lifting force given by the relation $!$F = k I^{2}$!$, where $!$F$!$ is the force in newtons, $!$I$!$ is the current in amperes, and $!$k$!$ is a constant equal to $!$0.5~\\text{N/A}^2$!$. If the electromagnet must provide a lifting force of $!$100~\\text{N}$!$ to successfully pick up iron scraps, calculate the minimum current $!$I$!$ (in amperes) required to achieve this force.",
