            "id": "54d1fb090a624d6593e18",
            "questionText": "A fishing game uses a strong permanent magnet on a fishing rod and a fish containing a weak permanent magnet. Given that the magnetic moments of the rod magnet and the fish magnet are $!$\\mu_1$!$ and $!$\\mu_2$!$ (in A\\cdot m^2) respectively, and that the centers of the magnets are separated by a distance $!$r$!$ (in m), compute the net magnetic force (in N) between the two magnets using the dipole-dipole interaction formula $!$F = \\frac{3\\mu_0}{4\\pi r^4}(\\mu_1\\mu_2)$!$, where $!$\\mu_0$!$ is the permeability of free space. Assume the alignment of the magnets is such that the force is attractive. Provide a single numerical answer for $!$F$!$. (If any values are missing, please provide them so that a numerical answer can be calculated.)",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "c3a8fa78ca604a2ba0703",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct interaction formula needed to calculate the net force between the two magnets. Please select the dipole-dipole interaction formula that should be used.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$F = \\frac{3\\mu_0}{4\\pi r^4}(\\mu_1\\mu_2)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
